body: I can this is a bug in the converter. You can have a PR for that, or we will fix it soon.

I think it's a bug caused by a missing converter/shape calculator for Dropout layer. To fix this problem, we need to add a converter (example is [here](https://github.com/onnx/onnxmltools/blob/master/onnxmltools/convert/keras/operator_converters/Dense.py)) and a shape calculator (example is [here](https://github.com/onnx/onnxmltools/blob/708d3091084da1acf42cf058161017e1152fa337/onnxmltools/convert/keras/shape_calculators/Lazy.py#L54)).
@wenbingl , @duli2012 , could you find someone to fix this problem? It's quite simple because Dropout is basically an identity operator in prediction phase.

@eraoul , using `None` for batch size is fine for runtime. It's officially supported by ONNX standard. Note that `None` means a variable-length dimension (think about speed recognition, the length of a sentence is always not deterministic)

Thanks for the quick feedback. I'll be looking forward to the fix!

BTW is there a list of supported operations somewhere to track this sort of thing? I expected Dropout to be supported; perhaps there are other ops that should be checked on as well to avoid similar errors?

@eraoul , good point! We should document the list down. @wenbingl , @duli2012 , could you add a doc string into [convert of Keras](https://github.com/onnx/onnxmltools/blob/708d3091084da1acf42cf058161017e1152fa337/onnxmltools/convert/keras/convert.py#L19) (like what we did for [sklearn](https://github.com/onnx/onnxmltools/blob/708d3091084da1acf42cf058161017e1152fa337/onnxmltools/convert/sklearn/convert.py#L23))?

Just for my planning, can you give me an estimate of when your team might be able to fix this Dropout bug? (e.g., days or weeks?) Also, will I need to re-build onnxmltools from source when this goes in or do you update the pip repo frequently?

Thanks in advance for the help!
We will fix it in the next week.

Thanks Wenbing, that's great news.  Does this mean I'll need to build from
source after the fix, or will it be fixed in the pip package on pypi?
